On Tue, 26 Aug 2003 tpollin(-at-)comcast.net wrote:

> I need badly to recover or replace the vinyl on the 2 front seats of my 73
> transporter. does anyone reccomend an economical solution. they seem to big to
> ship around the country to have done. are there ome good kits?

You can get upholstery kits that slide onto the seats like a glove.  The
procedure is, strip seats, fix springs, fix padding, slide upholstery over
the seats, reinstall, looks like OEM!

